{{Documentation subpage}}
{{High-use}}
{{Uses TemplateStyles|Template:Script/styles.css}}

This template applies custom styling (better typefaces and/or typefaces that support uncommon scripts and/or bigger size text) to scripts (writing systems).

=== Usage ===
This template takes two unnamed parameters: the [[ISO 15924#List of codes|ISO 15924]] alpha-4 code and the text to transform. Some scripts can also be identified by their name.

This template {{strong|does not mark up text as being X language}}. For instance, Hebrew text marked up using {{tlx|Script/Hebrew}} will be marked up as Hebrew {{em|script}}, but {{strong|not}} Hebrew {{em|text}}.

This means that {{strong|foreign-language text will not be invisibly marked up as a different language}} in the same manner as {{tlx|lang}} or {{tlx|transliteration}}. Non-English text {{em|needs}} to be marked up in [[Template:Language templates|language templates]] for [[:en:MOS:ACCESS|accessibility]]; see [[MOS:OTHERLANG]] for more details.

